<doc f='boost-1.85.0/libs/json/include/boost/json/value.hpp' l='2281'>/** Return a `bool` pointer if this is a boolean, else return `nullptr`

        If `this-&gt;kind() == kind::bool_`, returns a pointer
        to the underlying boolean. Otherwise, returns
        `nullptr`.

        @par Example
        The return value is used in both a boolean context and
        to assign a variable:
        @code
        if( auto p = jv.if_bool() )
            return *p;
        @endcode

        @par Complexity
        Constant.

        @par Exception Safety
        No-throw guarantee.
    */</doc>
